{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (A1 — anti-slop / over-engineering / NIH): no findings.\n\nAffirmations:\n- No new abstraction or dependency: the latency split rides on the recorder's existing per-step record structure via an ADDITIVE `duration_ms` field (executor._step_record), reconstructed in gate_dispatch._attach_plan_review_metrics from `rec.steps`. No parallel timing facility is invented; wall-clock uses stdlib `time.monotonic()`.\n- YAGNI / current done-definition: the metrics serve a stated, concrete need — reinstating the db7b AC5 coverage['metrics'] regression so the sidecar carries det_ms/llm_ms/total_ms/llm_calls/claim_path for passive latency/cost-target refinement. Not hypothetical.\n- NIH passes (and is the INTENDED lifecycle): this deliberately reconstructs the dict that B-RETIRE's removal of bespoke run_review dropped, retaining claim_path \"matching the db7b dict exactly\" rather than rebuilding a competing producer. The `llm_calls` cost proxy explicitly mirrors run_review's coverage-derived proxy (understood reuse, not cargo-cult). `criteria_count` is an existing batch-runner output (production_batch_runner.py:134, runners.py:136).\n- No config-surface proliferation: metrics are derived passively from run data; no new config key introduced.\n- DSO anti-pattern screen (golden-hammer / cargo-cult / resume-driven / premature-optimization): none observed — plain stdlib timing, scoped to one gate path, no trendy tech, no speculative optimization.\n\nClean chunk for A1."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782546153802672001,"uuid":"58cfe947-bcc5-4977-8beb-38aa51828bd6"}